42,148,148,158\n | y1Title=Total (cumulative)\n | y2Title=Active\n | y3Title=Recoveries\n}}\n'''Notes''':\n*There was no official report on 20 March 2020, [[Worldometer]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/venezuela/|title=Venezuela Coronavirus: 197 Cases and 9 Deaths - Worldometer|website=Worldometer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> and the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) of the [[Johns Hopkins University]] reported 65 cases, numbers coming from an article of ''[[El Nacional (Venezuela)|El Nacional]]'' from undisclosed sources from the Venezuelan Ministry of Health.<ref name=\":12\" />\n*The recoveries from 21 March to 25 March indicate people without symptoms for at least 5 days, considered as recovered in the official reports.<ref name=vtv21m />\n\n=== Confirmed deaths ===\n{{Graph\n|type=rect\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|height=300\n|colors= #000000 \n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Week (2020)\n|xAxisAngle=-90\n|x=13-19 March, 20-26March,27 March-2 April,3-9 April,10-16 April,17-23 April,24-30 April\n|yAxisTitle=New deaths per week\n|y1=0,1,{{#expr:5-1}},{{#expr:9-5}},0,1,0\n}}\n\n=== Regional distribution ===\nCases per federal entity touched by the pandemic, as of 3 May 2020:<ref name=EP3may>{{cite news|url=https://elpitazo.net/salud/venezuela-reporta-12-nuevos-casos-de-covid-19-este-3may/|title=Venezuela reporta 12 nuevos casos de COVID-19 este #3May|language=es|work=El Pitazo|date=3 May 2020|access-date=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable col3der\"\n!Federal entity\n!Number of reported cases\n!Confirmed deaths\n|-\n|{{flag|Anzo\u00e1tegui}}\n|4\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Apure}}\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Aragua}}\n|34\n|1\n|-\n|{{flag|Barinas}}\n|7\n|0\n|-\n|{{Flag|Bol\u00edvar}}\n|3\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Caracas|name=Capital District}}{{efn|The number of cases per region is inconsistent and may differ from source to source. In other sources, Capital District, Federal Dependencies, M\u00e9rida, Miranda, T\u00e1chira, Yaracuy and undisclosed locations, the number of cases may differ from the one reported in here.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://runrun.es/noticias/405886/delcy-rodriguez-confirma-2-nuevos-casos-de-covid-19-2/|title=Delcy Rodr\u00edguez confirma 2 nuevos casos de COVID-19|work=Runrunes|date=30 April 2020|access-date=30 April 2020|language=es}}</ref>|name=runrunesmap}}\n|32\n|4\n|-\n|{{Flag|Cojedes}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Falc\u00f3n}}\n|3\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Dependencias Federales|name=Federal Dependencies}}{{efn|name=runrunesmap}}{{Efn|The only affected federal dependency is [[Los Roques]]}}\n|4\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Gu\u00e1rico}}\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Lara}}\n|5\n|1\n|-\n|{{flag|M\u00e9rida}}{{efn|name=runrunesmap}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Miranda}}{{efn|name=runrunesmap}}\n|92\n|2\n|-\n|{{flag|Monagas}}\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Nueva Esparta}}\n|111\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Portuguesa}}\n|4\n|0\n|-\n|{{Flag|Sucre}}\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|{{Flag|T\u00e1chira}}{{efn|name=runrunesmap}}\n|19\n|1\n|-\n|{{Flag|Trujillo}}\n|7\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Vargas}}\n|15\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Yaracuy}}{{efn|name=runrunesmap}}\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|{{flag|Zulia}}\n|6\n|1\n|-\n|Undisclosed location{{efn|name=runrunesmap}}\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|-\n!Total\n!357\n!10\n|}\nVarious Venezuelan newspapers have pointed out that there have been some inconsistencies with the government reports by federal states.<ref name=\"runrunesactu26marzo\">{{Cite web|url=https://runrun.es/noticias/402336/delcy-rodriguez-confirma-primer-fallecido-por-covid-19/|title=Delcy Rodr\u00edguez confirma primer fallecido por Covid-19|date=26 March 2020|website=Runrun|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://runrun.es/rr-es-plus/402235/cronologia-de-incongruencias-y-opacidad-en-cifras-oficiales-de-coronavirus-19-en-venezuela/|title=Cronolog\u00eda de incongruencias y opacidad en cifras oficiales de Covid-19 en Venezuela|date=26 March 2020|website=Runrunes|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://efectococuyo.com/politica/importados-o-locales-contradicciones-del-chavismo-en-torno-a-los-casos-de-covid-19/|title=\u00bf\"Importados\" o locales?, contradicciones del chavismo en torno a los casos de COVID-19|last=Avenda\u00f1o|first=Shari|date=19 March 2020|website=Efecto Cocuyo|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":10\" /> For example, 24 March report differs from 23 report, as [[T\u00e1chira]] and [[Portuguesa (state)|Portuguesa]] that reported cases before, were no longer included.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://efectococuyo.com/coronavirus/maduro-informa-que-se-elevan-a-91-contagios-de-covid-19-y-dice-que-hay-casos-comunitarios/|title=Maduro informa que se elevan a 91 contagios de COVID-19 y dice que \"hay casos comunitarios\"|last=Rodr\u00edguez Rosas|first=Ronny|date=25 March 2020|website=Efecto Cocuyo|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=25 March 2020}}</ref> On 26 March, while the official report indicated 107 total cases, the number of cases per dependency amounted to 108.<ref name=\"runrunesactu26marzo\" />\n\nIn April, the Ministry of Public Health of [[Guyana]] confirmed patients with coronavirus in [[Barima-Waini]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stlucianewsonline.com/guyana-33-test-positive-for-covid-19/|title=Guyana: 33 test positive for COVID-19|last=Joseph|first=Sharine|date=8 April 2020|website=St. Lucia News Online|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.gov.gy/index.php/component/k2/item/133-14apr|title=Ministry of Public Health - Guyana COVID-19 Dashboard|website=Ministry of Public Health Guyana|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> located in [[Guayana Esequiba]] and a territory disputed with Venezuela. These cases are not included in the statistics provided by the Bolivarian Government of Venezuela.\n\n=== Per origin ===\nAs of 16 March, there were 33 confirmed cases in Venezuela. According to official estimates, among these, 28 came from [[Europe]] and 5 from [[C\u00facuta]], Colombia. Two of the cases consisted of foreign citizens, one of a diplomatic official, while the rest consisted of Venezuelan residents.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\nBy 22 March, Maduro announced out of all the 77 cases were imported.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://runrun.es/noticias/401873/maduro-anuncio-que-cifra-de-contagiados-por-covid-19-aumento-a-77/|title=Maduro anunci\u00f3 que cifra de contagiados por Covid-19 aument\u00f3 a 77|date=23 March 2020|website=Runrun.es|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> According to him, 43 had traveled recently, the distribution was as follows:<ref name=\":5\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable col3der\"\n!Country\n!Number of imported cases\n|-\n|{{flag|Brazil}}\n|2\n|-\n|{{flag|Colombia}}\n|10\n|-\n|{{flag|Dominican Republic}}\n|3\n|-\n|{{flag|Italy}}\n|3\n|-\n|{{flag|Peru}}\n|1\n|-\n|{{flag|Spain}}\n|21 \n|-\n|{{flag|United States}}\n|3\n|-\n!Total\n!43\n|}\nOn 24 March, Maduro first mentioned the existence of cases transmitted locally in the country.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://runrun.es/noticias/402104/maduro-anuncio-que-hay-7-nuevos-casos-de-coronavirus-para-este-24mar/|title=Maduro anunci\u00f3 que hay 7 nuevos casos de coronavirus para este #24Mar|date=24 March 2020|website=Runrunes|language=es|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2009 flu pandemic in Venezuela]]\n* [[2019 shipping of humanitarian aid to Venezuela]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Venezuela|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101008203535/http://www.mpps.gob.ve/ Ministerio del Poder Popular para la Salud] {{in lang|es}}\n*[http://coronavirusvenezuela.info/ Coronavirus - Presidencia Venezuela] {{in lang|es}}\n*[https://twitter.com/corona_virusven Coronavirus Venezuela on Twitter] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Crisis in Venezuela|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Venezuela| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country|Venezuela]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in South America|Venezuela]]\n[[Category:2020 in Venezuela|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Crisis in Venezuela]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Venezuela]]\n", "name_user": "RobertskySemi", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInternational sanctions:bypass redirect, replaced:UN High Commissioner for Human RightsMichelle Bacheletcalled for any sanctions imposed on Venezuela and other countries", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Venezuela"}
